# PageMessage

The Page Message component is a suggested action/service/data that users might find helpful, but isn\'t a business logic blocker or critical to their experience.
They can be vertically stacked and combined with other message types.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/page-message
```

```tsx
import { PageMessage } from '@ids-ts/page-message';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `actionLabel` | `string` | No | Value to be displayed on the action button, inline with the message |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Test automation ID. |
| `title` | `string` | Yes | - |
| `type` | `PageMessageType` | Yes | - |
| `dismissible` | `boolean` | Yes | - |
| `onActionClick` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | Callback when action button is clicked |
| `onClose` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | Callback when component is closed. |
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | - |
| `innerRef` | `((instance: HTMLDivElement \| null) => void) \| React.Ref<HTMLDivElement>` | No | Ref to forward to the container div. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface PageMessageProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** Value to be displayed on the action button, inline with the message */
  actionLabel?: string;
  /** Test automation ID. */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * Text to display as a heading for the message.
   *
   * @default ''
   */
  title: string;
  /**
   * Type of page message to display, shows an icon before the title
   * e.g. 'info', 'error', 'warning', 'discovery'
   *
   * @default 'info'
   */
  type: PageMessageType;
  /**
   * Shows close icon which allows the component to be closed.
   *
   * @default true
   */
  dismissible: boolean;
  /** Callback when action button is clicked */
  onActionClick?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /** Callback when component is closed. */
  onClose?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /**
   * Whether component is open.
   *
   * @default true
   */
  open: boolean;
  /** Ref to forward to the container div. */
  innerRef?:
    | ((instance: HTMLDivElement | null) => void)
    | React.RefObject<HTMLDivElement>
    | null
    | undefined;
}

export type PageMessageType =
  | 'success'
  | 'info'
  | 'error'
  | 'warn'
  | 'discovery';
```

</details>

